      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Panorama of Sarajevo’s old town on a slightly cloudy winter day, with the <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=V2">Vijećnica</ref> in the foreground. To its left, a small section of the Miljacka river is seen, in the background, a skyline of minarets. The roofs are covered with snow.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The cirrus clouds on this picture form an interesting pattern. The photograph is taken from the same spot as siba.4887. Analogue photographic process, negative-positive (Agfa Isopan 17 DIN). Original preserved as a negative-diptych, stored as a negative and a digital record.</ab>
